webpackJsonp([711549352439862e4],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/agile-build-measure-learn.json":function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>Build Measure Learn</h2>\n<p>Agile methodology is about how to build things right. “Build Measure Learn” is about how to build the right thing.</p>\n<p>The term comes from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lean_startup">Lean Startup methodology</a>, popularised by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eric_Ries">Eric Ries</a>, the author of <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Lean-Startup-Innovation-Successful-Businesses/dp/0670921602">The Lean Startup</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Build Measure Learn</strong> is sometimes referred to as Hypothesis Driven Development. </p>\n<h3>The Premise:</h3>\n<p>The goal of Build Measure Learn is to <em>build</em> a Minimum Viable Product (MVP), <em>measure</em> the impact of the MVP and <em>learn</em> about whether the Product that is being built is viable, valuable and fulfils the assumed success criteria.</p>\n<h4>More Information:</h4>\n<p><a href="https://steveblank.com/2015/05/06/build-measure-learn-throw-things-against-the-wall-and-see-if-they-work/">Why Build, Measure, Learn – isn’t just throwing things against the wall to see if they work – the Minimal Viable Product</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.mindtools.com/pages/article/build-measure-learn.htm">The Build-Measure-Learn Feedback Loop</a></p>',fields:{slug:"/agile/build-measure-learn/"},frontmatter:{title:"Build Measure Learn"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/agile/build-measure-learn/"}}}});
